           SPELL=procmeter
         VERSION=3.6
      PATCHLEVEL=1
          SOURCE="${SPELL}3-${VERSION}.tgz"
         SOURCE2=$SOURCE.pgp
   SOURCE_URL[0]=http://www.gedanken.demon.co.uk/download-${SPELL}/${SOURCE}
  SOURCE2_URL[0]=${SOURCE_URL[0]}.pgp
      SOURCE_GPG=procmeter.gpg:$SOURCE2:UPSTREAM_KEY
SOURCE_DIRECTORY="${BUILD_DIRECTORY}/${SPELL}3-${VERSION}"
        WEB_SITE="http://www.gedanken.demon.co.uk/download-procmeter/procmeter3-3.5c.tgz"
      LICENSE[0]=GPL
         ENTERED=20101229
           SHORT="a user information display and system status monitor"
cat << EOF
The ProcMeter program itself is a framework on which a number of modules
(plugins) are loaded. More modules can be written as required to perform
more monitoring and informational functions.

The statistics that are displayed are grouped by module, with a menu allowing
selection of module and a sub-menu for each output available for that module.

There are modules for APM, disk usage, memory, log files, network, sensors
and many other data sources.
EOF
